<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 06 at 9:38AM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Murray,
northeastern Floyd, south central Whitfield, southeastern Walker and
northwestern Gordon Counties through 1015 AM EDT...
At 938 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Lake Marvin, or 8 miles
northwest of Calhoun, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Calhoun, Resaca, Sugar Valley, Redbud, Lake Marvin, Tilton,
Nickelsville, and Audubon.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
